<h2>WP Tinylytics Shortcodes</h2>

<p>WP Tinylytics comes comes with a variety of shortcodes which can be embedded directly in a post, page, or theme block to reduce the need for extensive HTML customizations.</p>

<table class="form-table" role="presentation" style="width:100%;">
    <tr><th style="width:25%;">[tinykudos]</th><td>Displays an interactive button to track "kudos" given by readers. Best used directly in posts and pages.</td></tr>
	<tr><th>[tinyhits]</th><td>Displays a count of page loads of the page viewed. Best used directly in posts and pages.</td></tr>
	<tr><th>[tinystats]</th><td>Displays both overall site hits and uptime (<em>Note: a Tinylytics subscription is required to display uptime</em>). Best used in the footer of your site.</td></tr>
	<tr><th>[tinywebring]</th><td>Displays a random link to a Tinylytics webring site. Enabling the "Display webring avatars?" option will include the avatar if the site has one. Best used in the footer of your site.</td></tr>
	<tr><th>[tinyflags]</th><td>Displays flags from all the countries of site visitors. Best used in the footer of your site.</td></tr>
</table>

<p>Learn how to use the <a href="https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/shortcode-block/" target="_blank">Shortcode Block</a> in your theme. More information about <a href="https://tinylytics.app" target="_blank">Tinylytics</a> can be found in the <a href="https://tinylytics.app/docs" target="_blank">documentation</a>.</p>